[[File:Acacia farnesciana-- Sweet Acacia (27411624526).jpg|thumb|An '''opopanax''' tree, {{taxlink|Acacia farnesciana|species}}]]

===Etymology===
Borrowed from {{bor|en|la|opopanax}}, from Hellenistic Greek {{m|grc|ὀποπάναξ}}, from {{der|en|grc|ὀπός|t=vegetable juice}} + {{m|grc|πάναξ|t=any of several plants believed to have medicinal benefits}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|en|/əˈpɒpənaks/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~|es}}

# {{lb|en|obsolete}} A gum [[resin]] obtained from the root of {{taxlink|Opopanax chironium|species|noshow=1|ver=161118}}, formerly used in medicine.
# A [[perfume]] made from the gum resin of various trees.
#* '''2006''', {{w|Thomas Pynchon}}, ''{{w|Against the Day}}'', Vintage 2007, p. 450:
#*: they were hit by a strong polyaromatic gust [...] which included alcohol fumes, tobacco and hemp-smoke, a spectrum of inexpensive scent in which '''opopanax''' and vervain figured prominently
# The [[popinac]] or {{vern|opopanax tree}} ({{taxlink|Acacia farnesiana|species|noshow=1|ver=161118}}, syn. ''[[Vachellia farnesiana]]''), an [[acacia]] of America.

